		<legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
		<official-title>To direct the Secretary of the Treasury to develop and submit class life recommendations for
			 depreciable assets.</official-title>
	</form>
	<legis-body id="H09680E075AA64058B916A17AEAC09DA5" style="OLC">
		<section id="H0ABA9B7F55434469B1232D87B74635DF" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short title</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the <quote>
          <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Jobs Investment Act of 2014" proposed="true">Jobs Investment Act of 2014</cato:entity-ref>
        </quote>.</text>
		</section>
    <section id="H0D0CBA4CDF45492F9157F38E81947ACC">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Class life recommendations</header>
			<subsection id="HC8350ADCD3AB4CE4BD6DDD5FFB556747">
        <enum>(a)</enum>
        <header>In general</header>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">The <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-id="2000" entity-type="federal-body">Secretary of the Treasury</cato:entity-ref> shall, based on the monitoring and analysis of actual experience with
			 respect to depreciable property under <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Internal Revenue Code of 1986/s:168/ss:i/p:1">section 168(i)(1) of the Internal
			 Revenue Code of 1986</cato:entity-ref>, develop recommendations for prescribing to any
			 depreciable property a class life, classification, or recovery period that
			 more equitably provides for capital cost recovery across all industries
			 without any significant effect on total tax revenue.</text>
			</subsection>
      <subsection id="H54394EDFD79A4161899E6B4C1C7475B1">
        <enum>(b)</enum>
        <header>Proposal</header>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">Not later than January 31, 2019, and every 5 years thereafter, the <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="federal-body" entity-id="2000">Secretary</cato:entity-ref> shall submit to the
			 <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-id="HWM00" entity-type="committee">Committee on Ways and Means of the House of Representatives</cato:entity-ref> and the
			 <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-id="SSFI00" entity-type="committee">Committee on Finance of the Senate</cato:entity-ref> the recommendations developed under
			 <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Jobs Investment Act of 2014/s:2/ss:a" proposed="true">subsection (a)</cato:entity-ref>.</text>
			</subsection>
    </section>
  </legis-body>
